{"questionId":"19614","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A large underground tank is constructed at Mills Airport to store fuel. The tank is in the shape of an isosceles trapezoidal prism, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ABCDEFGH</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>70</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math> , <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AF</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>200</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AD</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>BC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>CD</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>110</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>. Angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ADC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp;and angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>BCD</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo></math>. The tank is illustrated below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/52f5ddf6013868370a25d6b7ddfe6ffc5b53643a.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>, the height of the tank.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mn>40</mn></mfrac></math><strong>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; </strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mn>20</mn></mfrac></math><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for correct substitutions in trig ratio.</p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>20</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>40</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><msqrt><msup><mn>40</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>20</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfenced></math><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em>&nbsp;for correct substitutions in Pythagoras’ theorem.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>34</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mtext>m</mtext></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mn>1200</mn></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>20</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>34</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6410</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em><em>(G2)</em></strong></p>\n<p><br><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19614","referenceCode":"20N.2.SL.TZ0.T_5a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find h, the height of the tank.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}